takes self-indulgence to a whole new level
Interesting view of how films get made, who are the decision-makers, and when these choices get made.  Recommend!
Get to unveil where the real power in filmmaking is. Again, it's all about the money, honey!
While at Cannes James Toback and Alec Baldwin pitch a fictitious movie project to numerous money folks giving an insider look at how movies get made.
Every filmmaker, big or small is chasing production money.
One of the best meta non fiction films on the inner workings of the film world.  Recommended to anyone who is interested in that wonderfully dysfunctional endeavor.
A mesmerizing score, beautiful cinematography, and candid interviews make this essential viewing for those who love film.
